<h2 id="200">2. Saving the search settings</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>When you start a search, your search settings are displayed up top as so-called “chips”.
You can save these search settings to apply them again more quickly and easily in the future.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="300">2.1. Saving the current filters</h3>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Start a search.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Saved filters</strong> (<span class="icon "><i class="material-bookmarks"></i></span>).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <span class="icon "><i class="material-bookmark_border"></i></span> <strong>Save current filter</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a name and toggle the optional settings as needed (<span class="icon blue"><i class="material-toggle_on"></i></span>).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.<br>
→ The filter settings now appear under <strong>Saved filters</strong> (<span class="icon "><i class="material-bookmarks"></i></span>).</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="imageblock">
<div class="content">
<img src="{{plugin_path('PlentyManual')}}/images/item/new-ui/assets/save-filters.gif" alt="save filters">
</div>
</div>
