<h2 id="600">4. FAQ</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="700">4.1. General questions</h3>
<div class="openblock collapseBox">
<div class="title"><strong>How can I give feedback?</strong></div>
<div class="content">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you want to give feedback about the new item UI, then please use <a href="https://forum.plentymarkets.com/c/item/18">this forum category</a>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="openblock collapseBox">
<div class="title"><strong>Will the old item UI be removed soon?</strong></div>
<div class="content">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>No.
The old item UI will not be removed in the near future.
For now, both the old and new item UI can be used in parallel.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="openblock collapseBox">
<div class="title"><strong>Which functions are still missing?</strong></div>
<div class="content">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The following functions are missing and are planned for the future:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>Create new items</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Generate variations</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Delete items</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Delete variations</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Item sets</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Multipacks</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Generate labels</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Item preview / Variation preview</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Serial numbers</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Item group function and variation group function</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The following functions are missing and are not planned for the future:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>Characteristics</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Free text fields</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Item tab: Media</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Item tab: Statistics</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="800">4.2. Searching for items</h3>
<div class="openblock collapseBox">
<div class="title"><strong>What are the default search settings? Are only active items searched by default?</strong></div>
<div class="content">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>No filters are set by default.</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>If you start the search without setting any filters, then all items will appear in the results.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Both active and inactive items are included in the search results by default.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="openblock collapseBox">
<div class="title"><strong>Can I import and export the search filter settings?</strong></div>
<div class="content">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>There is not an import / export function.
However, you can <a href="/en/item/new-ui/search#200">save your frequently used search settings</a>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="openblock collapseBox">
<div class="title"><strong>What do the operators in front of the search filters mean? IN, NOT IN, =, ≈</strong></div>
<div class="content">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>When you <a href="/en/item/new-ui/search#100">search for items and variations</a>, you’ll see these operators in front of some search fields.
They tell you which data records will be included in the search results.</p>
</div>
<table class="tableblock frame-all grid-all stretch">
<colgroup>
<col style="width: 16.6666%;">
<col style="width: 83.3334%;">
</colgroup>
<thead>
<tr>
<th class="tableblock halign-left valign-top">Operator</th>
<th class="tableblock halign-left valign-top">Explanation</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>IN</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">The search results include data records that match your selection.
Example: Products that are linked to a specific client.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>NOT IN</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">The search results include data records that do not match your selection.
Example: Products that are not linked to a specific client.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>=</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Is equal to.
Example: Search for the variation with the number 100.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>≈</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Contains.
Example: Search for all of the variations that have a number containing 100, e.g. 1001, 410037, 100, ABC-41003-D.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
